eventsAnnotated.name: 2013 Manila Floods
eventsAnnotated.description: Severe Tropical Storm Trami, known in the Philippines as Tropical Storm Maring, was a tropical cyclone that brought heavy rains to Taiwan and East China during mid-August 2013. The user is a response officer responsible for Metro Manila, one of the three defined metropolitan areas of the Philippines. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_Storm_Trami_%282013%29' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2015 Paris Attacks
eventsAnnotated.description: The November 2015 Paris attacks were a series of coordinated terrorist attacks that occurred on Friday, 13 November 2015 in Paris, France and the city's northern suburb, Saint-Denis. The user is a response officer in the France's command and control center who is just recieving reports of an explosion in Paris. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/November_2015_Paris_attacks' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2012 Italy Earthquake
eventsAnnotated.description: In May 2012, two major earthquakes struck Northern Italy, known as the 2012 Emilia earthquakes. The user is a response officer in the command and control center responsible for responding to the earthquakes as they unfold. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_Northern_Italy_earthquakes' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2013 Queensland Flood
eventsAnnotated.description: Tropical Cyclone Oswald in January 2013 passed over parts of Queensland and New South Wales, Australia causing widespread impact including severe storms, flooding, and water spouts. The user is a response officer in the central Australia command and control center responsible for the event. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclone_Oswald' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: DEMO: CrisisLex26 2012 Colorado wildfires
eventsAnnotated.description: The 2012 Colorado wildfires were an unusually devastating series of Colorado wildfires, including several separate fires that occurred throughout June, July, and August 2012. At least 34,500 residents were evacuated in June. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_Colorado_wildfires' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>
